pr_review_body:
Lots of changes. So, this is a major refactoring job.
Probably it would be a good idea to change the title;
`Add {set,get}_bucket_versioning() APIs`

I left some initial comments; 

High level comment is; 

- The manager class APIs seem a bit brittle (especially with cache). Can we use ABCClass to have abstract methods? I also think we should hide cache behind the manager's create/delete APIs. It seems doable in the first glance, but lmk if you think it can't be
- Cache means the agent becomes stateful, which means the behavior after agent restarts is undefined. Is there a design for how to handle this? Also, if we don't handle this right now, can we make this feature off by default? We shouldn't have non-fully working feature just for the sake of performance optimization, especially when the feature is already GA

@LongnoseRob very big job. Unfortunately, I suspect something went wrong during rebasing of the pull request and some not relevant files result modified. I am not a GIT guru, but I would recommend to have a look at this page for the pull request rebase: https://docs.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-pull-requests/incorporating-changes-from-a-pull-request/about-pull-request-merges#rebase-and-merge-your-pull-request-commits
Also, this may be helpful: https://github.com/edx/edx-platform/wiki/How-to-Rebase-a-Pull-Request

In any case, thanks for your incredible amount of work and dedication

Delete button should be moved inside expansion panel with `slot="icons"` instead of absolute position.

Also the same style as `ha-automation-action-row` can be applied to title.

```css
h3 {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: inherit;
  font-weight: inherit;
}
 ```
